COMPILING AND INSTALLING ON *NIX
================================
Packages for *NIX aren't currently provided. You could always ask your distros 
development team to add matrixgl to their repositories, if you don't like 
compiling yourself. 

To extract the source code, fire up a terminal, cd into your download 
directory and type the following commands:
   $tar xzf nsuds-0.1B.tar.gz
   $cd nsuds-0.1B

Then, to compile and install, run the following commands:
   $./configure
   $make
   (Then, as root)
   #make install

You can then run nsuds from any terminal.


REMOVING NSUDS
==============
To remove nsuds, cd to the source directory and type the following as root:
#make uninstall
Which will remove any added files. 


IN-GAME KEYS
============
q       - Quit
n       - New Game
p       - Pause Game
1-9     - Enter number in selected square
wasd   \  
hjkl    - Move between squares 
Arrows /

SUPPORTED OPERATING SYSTEMS
===========================
matrixgl is currently in beta, but it has been confirmed to work on the following platforms:
   . Linux: Gentoo
   . Linux: Ubuntu


